Populate the world for this story. You are creating the CAST and the DILEMMAS —
the raw dramatic material every later stage builds from. The cast is effectively
locked after this stage: anyone who matters must exist now.

You are supplying ingredients, not finishing a story: a later triage keeps the
cohesive ensemble and cuts what doesn't connect. Don't pad toward completeness —
every entity you invent must earn its place by anchoring a dilemma (an entity no
dilemma needs is a triage cut waiting to happen, however vivid its concept).

VISION:
- Premise: {{ vision.premise }}
- Genre: {{ vision.genre }}{% if vision.subgenre %} ({{ vision.subgenre }}){% endif %}
- Tone: {{ vision.tone }}
- Themes: {{ vision.themes | join("; ") }}
{% if vision.content_notes.include %}- Embrace: {{ vision.content_notes.include | join("; ") }}{% endif %}
{% if vision.content_notes.avoid %}- Avoid: {{ vision.content_notes.avoid | join("; ") }}{% endif %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- Between {{ scope.cast_min }} and {{ scope.cast_max }} entities. Ids are category-prefixed
  slugs: character:..., location:..., object:..., faction:... (lowercase, hyphens).
  Each entity gets a name, a one-sentence concept, and optionally a few base details
  (appearance, manner) as key-value pairs. Characters also get pronouns
  ("she/her", "they/them", …) — prose will be held to them exactly.
- Every entity must be in some dilemma's anchored_to. Fewer entities that all
  matter beat a full roster with passengers.
- Exactly {{ scope.hard_dilemmas }} HARD dilemma(s) and {{ scope.soft_dilemmas }} SOFT dilemma(s).
  A dilemma is a binary dramatic question where BOTH answers are compelling and
  choosing costs something. Hard dilemmas are the backbone: they commit near the
  climax and their outcomes never reconverge. Soft dilemmas are subplots: they
  resolve mid-story and storylines rejoin afterward.
- Each dilemma: id (dilemma:slug), the question, why_it_matters (the stakes — what
  lasting mark the choice leaves), role (hard/soft), residue_weight (heavy/light/
  cosmetic — how much prose must differ where arcs share structure), ending_salience
  (high/low/none — how much endings differ by this choice), exactly TWO answers
  (id answer:slug + one-sentence text; the answers are equals — neither is a default),
  and anchored_to: the entity ids central to it.
- At least two dilemmas must share an anchored entity, or the story becomes
  parallel novels instead of a woven world.
